                  </persName>
            , ordinary and minister.''</p>
               <p>Q. for Crown. Was you by when this was sign'd and fill'd up?</p>
               <p>Philips. I was.</p>
               <p>Q. for Crown. Have you often banns published for people that do not live in the precinct ?</p>
               <p>Philips. We often have.</p>
               <p>Q. for Crown. Did you ever read the rubrick in the common prayer book before the order of matrimony ?</p>
               <p>Philips. I cannot say.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17551204-39-verdict214" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17551204-39-verdict214" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>See him tried in Sir 
